==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] '''[[cultura]]''', from '''[[cultus]]''', perfect passive participle  of '''[[colere]]''', ''till, cultivate, worship''.
<br>From [[Greek]] '''[[άνθρωπος]]''' (anthropos), ''man, human being'' + Greek '''[[λόγος]]''', ''word, saying, speech, discourse''.

===Noun phrase===
''cultural anthropology'', or ''social anthropology'', or ''socio-cultural anthropology''

# one of four commonly recognized fields of [[anthropology]].

